Actress Folorunsho Adeola aka Arike Gold has said adopting polygamy is an effective way to solve infidelity in marriage. Though the actress expressed support for polygamy having been born into one, she insisted she wouldn’t be involved in one, which is why she won’t marry a married man. When asked during an interview with Sunday Scoop if she agrees polygamy is a solution to infidelity, Arike Gold responded: “Yes, I agree. But, that does not mean I will marry a married man.”   Regina Chukwu threatens to beat celebrities who campaign for…     Why I underwent plastic surgery, by Mercy Eke     Helen Paul reveals academic secret   Explaining her stance, she stated: “Most times, ladies just want to have their own kids. Some of these ladies who are not first wives are comfortable and doing well for themselves; they are not just lucky with men. So, they end up having children for married men.” The actress also urged people to keep their lives private lifestyle to minimise drama. She added: “The saying that ‘a private life is a happy life’ is definitely true. If what people know about one is limited, it will be difficult for them to start a rumour about one or about people close to one. “I cannot stop people from gossiping about me. But, a private life minimises drama. I don’t share details of my life on social media because I feel it should be kept private.”